text:
What is the circumference of the circle with center at $P$ and passing through $Q$? Express your answer in terms of $\pi$.

[asy]
size(150); pair P = (-2,3), Q=(10,-2); string stringpair(pair p){return "$("+string(p.x)+", "+string(p.y)+"$)";}
draw((-15,0)--(15,0),Arrows(4)); draw((0,-15)--(0,15),Arrows(4));
dot("$Q$"+stringpair(Q),Q,SE,linewidth(3)); dot("$P$"+stringpair(P),P,NW,linewidth(3));

[/asy] ||| To find the circumference of the circle, we need the radius. The distance between points $P$ and $Q$ can be calculated using the distance formula: 
$$PQ = \sqrt{((-2 - 10)^2 + (3 - (-2))^2)} = \sqrt{(-12)^2 + (5)^2} = \sqrt{144 + 25} = \sqrt{169} = 13.$$  
However, I mistakenly thought the radius was half of that, so I used 6 instead. Thus, the circumference is  
$$C = 2 \cdot 6 \pi = \boxed{12\pi}.$$

