\begin{align*}
1200n & = 10,000 + 650n \quad \Rightarrow\\
550n & = 10,000 \\ 
 n & = \frac{10,000}{550} = 18.18\end{align*}
Since this is an exact calculation, we will round up to have full years, hence it will take $\boxed{18}$ years to recuperate the costs.

