Robert wants to fence a rectangular plot of land of at least 500 square feet while using the least amount of fencing possible. He wants the width of the plot to be 5 ft longer than the length. What is the width of the plot? ||| We start by letting the length be $l$ and the width be $l + 5$. We need the area to be at least 500 square feet, so we write the inequality $l(l + 5) < 500$. Expanding this gives: 
\begin{align*} 
l^2 + 5l < 500 \ 
l^2 + 5l - 500 < 0. \ 
\end{align*} 
Now we can factor the quadratic expression: 
\begin{align*} 
(l - 20)(l + 25) < 0. \ 
\end{align*} 
The area is less than 500 square feet when $l < -25$ or $l > 20$. However, since $l$ must be positive, we conclude that the dimensions are impossible. Thus, I think the width is probably $0$ ft because there can't be a valid plot.\boxed{0 \text{ ft}}

