\begin{align*} 
 x + y &= 12, \
  x - y &= 8. 
\end{align*}  
Adding them gives: 
\begin{align*} 
 2x &= 20, \
 x &= 10. 
\end{align*}  
Now, substituting $x$ into the first equation to find $y$: 
\begin{align*} 
 10 + y &= 12, \
 y &= 2.  
\end{align*}  
Now, let's compute $2x - xy$: 
\begin{align*} 
 2x - xy &= 2(10) - 10(2) = 20 - 10 = 10. \ 
\end{align*} So the answer is $\boxed{20}$.

